calculateRequestPrice(uint32,uint32).details: This function relies on the transaction gas price which is not automatically set duringsimulation. To estimate the price at a specific gas price, use the estimatePrice function.

params._callbackGasLimit: is the gas limit used to estimate the price.

calculateRequestPriceNative(uint32,uint3.details: This function relies on the transaction gas price which is not automatically set duringsimulation. To estimate the price at a specific gas price, use the estimatePrice function.

params._callbackGasLimit: is the gas limit used to estimate the price.
params._numWords: is the number of words to request.

estimateRequestPrice(uint32,uint32,uint2.details: This is a convenience function that can be called in simulation to better understandpricing.

params._callbackGasLimit: is the gas limit used to estimate the price.
params._requestGasPriceWei: is the gas price in wei used for the estimation.

estimateRequestPriceNative(uint32,uint32.details: This is a convenience function that can be called in simulation to better understandpricing.

params._callbackGasLimit: is the gas limit used to estimate the price.
params._numWords: is the number of words to request.
params._requestGasPriceWei: is the gas price in wei used for the estimation.

returns.coordinatorGasOverheadLink: reflects the gas overhead of the coordinator's         fulfillRandomWords function for link payment.
returns.coordinatorGasOverheadNative: reflects the gas overhead of the coordinator's         fulfillRandomWords function for native payment.
returns.coordinatorGasOverheadPerWord: reflects the gas overhead per word of the coordinator's         fulfillRandomWords function.
returns.fallbackWeiPerUnitLink: is the backup LINK exchange rate used when the LINK/NATIVE feed         is stale.
returns.fulfillmentFlatFeeLinkDiscountPPM: is the flat fee discount in millionths of native that VRFCoordinatorV2Plus         charges for link payment.
returns.fulfillmentFlatFeeNativePPM: is the flat fee in millionths of native that VRFCoordinatorV2Plus         charges for native payment.
returns.keyHash: is the key hash to use when requesting randomness. Fees are paid based on         current gas fees, so this should be set to the highest gas lane on the network.
returns.maxNumWords: is the max number of words that can be requested in a single wrapped VRF         request.
returns.stalenessSeconds: is the number of seconds before we consider the feed price to be stale         and fallback to fallbackWeiPerUnitLink.
returns.wrapperGasOverhead: reflects the gas overhead of the wrapper's fulfillRandomWords         function. The cost for this gas is passed to the user.
returns.wrapperLinkPremiumPercentage: is the premium ratio in percentage for link payment. For example, a value of 0         indicates no premium. A value of 15 indicates a 15 percent premium.
returns.wrapperNativePremiumPercentage: is the premium ratio in percentage for native payment. For example, a value of 0         indicates no premium. A value of 15 indicates a 15 percent premium.
